net.trajano.ms.gateway.handlers

Class AuthenticatedClientValidator

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.trajano.ms.gateway.handlers.SelfRegisteringRoutingContextHandler
      • net.trajano.ms.gateway.handlers.AuthenticatedClientValidator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    io.vertx.core.Handler<io.vertx.ext.web.RoutingContext>

    @Component
 @Order(value=1)
public class AuthenticatedClientValidator
extends SelfRegisteringRoutingContextHandler

    Handles determining what Origin URIs are allowed based on the Origin and Authorization header. If the authorization is Basic, then the client ID and secret are verified against the system. If it is a Bearer authorization, it will use the aud value of the data referenced by the access token.

    Author:
    Archimedes Trajano
